<P>
 California became the largest milk-producing state in August, but nobody much 
noticed. "In Wisconsin, dairy is a way of life," state legislator and dairy 
farmer Rusty Areias explained to the Wall Street Journal. "Here in California, 
dairy is a business." CHARLES PERRY 
