COMMUNITY COLLEGES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Apparently, enrollment in state community colleges is down 9% (Dec. 23). 
</P>
<P>
 After several attempts to enroll myself and my wife in two emeritus classes at 
Saddleback College (totaling about a day -- half standing in lines at the 
campus and another half with automated telephone registration), I gave up. The 
hurdles and bureaucracy were overwhelming. 
</P>
<P>
 I admire those students who persist -- my interests were thwarted by the 
system. 
</P>
<P>
 ROBERT G. HOWARD 
</P>
<P>
 San Clemente 
