<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; ON OFF-NIGHT, ARIZONA BEATS ARIZONA STATE BY 17 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Damon Stoudamire scored 30 points and Khalid Reeves added 24 as No. 9 Arizona 
struggled through an off-night to beat Arizona State, 98-81, Wednesday night at 
Tucson. 
</P>
<P>
 The Wildcats (11-1), who turned in their finest game of the season last 
Thursday with a 119-95 victory over then-No. 7 Michigan, played lethargically 
in the first 20 minutes and led only 37-31 at halftime despite a 35-19 
rebounding advantage. 
</P>
<P>
 But then they got their fast break going and outscored Arizona State, 21-4, to 
open the second half with Reeves leading the way. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 1 Arkansas 87, Mississippi 61 -- Clint McDaniel made three steals during a 
20-0 run that lifted the Razorbacks at Fayetteville, Ark. 
</P>
<P>
 The Rebels (5-4) went scoreless for more than six minutes in the first half. 
During a four-minute span, Mississippi got only one shot out of eight 
possessions. When the run ended with 9:56 left in the half, Arkansas (10-0) 
led, 25-5. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 2 North Carolina 88, North Carolina State 58 -- The Tar Heels started the 
second half with an 18-5 run and finally found their touch from the foul line 
to win at Chapel Hill. 
</P>
<P>
 The Tar Heels (11-1) won their ninth consecutive game and have defeated the 
Wolfpack (4-7) by an average of 36 points over the last three meetings. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 5 Kansas 90, North Carolina Asheville 44 -- Steve Woodberry scored 16 
points to lead the Jayhawks to their 10th consecutive victory, at Lawrence, 
Kan. 
</P>
<P>
 Woodberry hit two short jump shots and a three-pointer in a 28-6 run early in 
the second half for Kansas (14-1). 
</P>
<P>
 No. 10 Purdue 68, Northwestern 67 -- Glenn Robinson, shut out for the first 7 
1/2 minutes, scored 34 points, including the winning basket with nine seconds 
left, to lead the Boilermakers at Evanston, Ill. 
</P>
<P>
 Purdue (12-0) went ahead, 66-61, on Robinson's three-pointer. But Pat Baldwin 
made three consecutive baskets as the Wildcats (9-1) took a 67-66 lead with 40 
seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 13 Michigan 75, Michigan State 64 -- Dugan Fife made two three-pointers in 
a decisive second-half burst and finished with a career-high 13 points to lead 
the Wolverines at Ann Arbor. 
</P>
<P>
 The Wolverines (9-2) never trailed, but they couldn't put Michigan State away 
until the Spartans (9-4) went cold over the final 10:47. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 17 Cincinnati 103, Chicago State 49 -- LaZelle Durden scored 33 points as 
Cincinnati beat Chicago State at Cincinnati. 
</P>
<P>
 Durden, coming off a 39-point game against Austin Peay, scored 17 in the first 
half as Cincinnati (11-2) pulled away to a 45-17 lead over Chicago State 
(1-12). 
</P>
<P>
 No. 25 Marquette 79, Memphis State 67 -- Damon Key scored 18 points and Roney 
Eford added 16 at Milwaukee to lead Marquette (8-3). Memphis State (5-5) was 
led by Justin Wimmer's 17 points. OTHER GAMES 
</P>
<P>
 Eric Williams scored 21 points off the bench to lead Providence (7-2) to an 
85-61 victory over Seton Hall (7-3) at Providence, R.I. . . . Kansas State 
(10-1) scored the last 11 points in a 67-63 victory over La Salle at 
Philadelphia. . . . Jeff Webster scored 35 points to lead Oklahoma (8-2) to a 
118-91 victory over Baylor (8-3) at Norman, Okla. . . . Dan Cross' layup with 
18 seconds left gave Florida (10-2) a 74-73 victory over Louisiana State (6-3) 
at Gainesville, Fla. . . . Tom Kleinschmidt scored 24 points as DePaul (9-1) 
took a 105-70 victory over Maine at Rosemont, Ill. . . . Emmett Hall scored 24 
points to lead South Carolina (4-5) to an 82-66 victory over Alabama (3-5) at 
Columbia, S.C. 
</P>
</TEXT>
