<TEXT>
<P>
 Leodes Van Buren of Newbury Park High, the state's all-time leading pass 
receiver, has left the Panthers' basketball team, first-year Coach Paul Coffman 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Van Buren, a 6-foot, 190-pound senior forward, said he was concerned about 
sustaining an injury and hurting his chances for a football scholarship. 
</P>
<P>
 "Plus, I want to put on some weight and I can't really do that playing 
basketball," Van Buren said. "I'm not going (to earn a scholarship) in 
basketball." 
</P>
<P>
 As a junior, Van Buren averaged team-leading numbers in rebounding (6.2) and 
steals (2.6), and finished second in scoring (14.3). 
</P>
<P>
 Colorado, Nebraska, San Diego State and Fresno State are among the schools 
recruiting Van Buren. JASON H. REID 
