<HEADLINE>
<P>
OFF THE TICKER: SMOKERS LOSE PLACE TO PARK THEIR BUTTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chrysler Corp.'s new compact sedans will be the first mass-market cars since 
the days of crank-start engines to come off the assembly line without ashtrays. 
</P>
<P>
 The third-biggest U.S. auto maker plans to offer the ashtray and a cigarette 
lighter as options on its sedans this year, making room for a coffee mug rest 
and a hookup for a cellular phone. 
</P>
<P>
 "Research shows that something like 78% of people who ride in cars don't 
smoke, so why should it be easier for the minority that does?" said Suzanne 
Hofmann, interior designer of the Chrysler Cirrus and Dodge Stratus. 
</P>
</TEXT>
