<P>
 SLOW DEATH: It's been two years since a death sentence was handed down in 
Ventura County, but prosecutors are trying to send two more men to the gas 
chamber: Christopher Sattiewhite, on trial for a 1992 slaying, and Mark Scott 
Thornton, accused of a killing last year (B1). . . . Neither needs to worry 
about cyanide pellets dropping into acid any time soon. The county's 
longest-serving Death Row inmate -- Alejandro Gilbert Ruiz, sentenced in 1980 
-- still has five years worth of appeals, prosecutor Richard Holmes said. . . . 
Ruiz's appeal faults a psychiatric report. Since he practiced voodoo, he says, 
he should have had a voodoo psychiatrist. 
