<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: YORBA LINDA; COUNTY'S EL TORO PROPOSAL OPPOSED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DANIELLE A. FOUQUETTE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council has voted to support Anaheim in its opposition to the County 
Board of Supervisors' proposal for an agency to plan the redevelopment of the 
El Toro Marine Corps Air Station. 
</P>
<P>
 But it stopped short of joining with any of the alternative organizations 
being formed. 
</P>
<P>
 The council voted to join Anaheim in protesting the formation of a nine-member 
panel composed of the five supervisors, three representatives from Irvine and 
one from Lake Forest. 
</P>
<P>
 "If we are going to have a voice in whatever (uses the base is put to), we had 
better stand up now and object with Anaheim," said Councilman John M. 
Gullixson. 
</P>
<P>
 Mayor Barbara Kiley, who serves as the city's representative to the League of 
California Cities, was authorized by the council to oppose the supervisors' 
plan when the league considers its position on the subject next week. 
</P>
<P>
 But the council specifically restricted Kiley from committing the city to any 
such alternative plan as the Orange County Regional Airport Authority, formed 
by Garden Grove, Los Alamitos and Stanton, which Anaheim is considering 
joining. DANIELLE A. FOUQUETTE 
</P>
</TEXT>
