1 KILLED, CAR SEVERED IN FREEWAY CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An unidentified person was killed and a car severed in a freeway crash 
Wednesday night, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Part of the car was left in a traffic lane, with the remainder on the 
shoulder, according to a California Highway Patrol dispatcher. The occupant of 
the car died en route to the hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident occurred at 9 p.m. and involved a second car, the CHP said. 
Information on that driver was not immediately available.  
</P>
<P>
 Three southbound lanes of the San Diego Freeway just north of Seal Beach 
Boulevard were blocked for more than an hour. 
