<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS: PACIFIC SYMPHONY RETURNS TO STUDIO; SPURS GOES ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ZAN DUBIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Pacific Symphony will start work next month on its first recording in 
seven years, an album for Koch International Classics that will include John 
Corigliano's Piano Concerto and two works, "Radiant Voices" and "Postcard," by 
Frank Ticheli, the orchestra's composer-in-residence. Production costs are 
