<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: SAN MARINO; FOUNDATION SETS NEW GOAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An education foundation is hoping to raise a record $750,000 by the end of the 
summer semester for the city's school district.  
</P>
<P>
 The San Marino Schools Foundation has set the goal $250,000 higher than the 
amount it raised for 1992-93.The foundation is already on its way to its goal. 
Contributions are up 32% compared to this time last year, foundation officials 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Since it was formed 14 years ago, the foundation has raised more than $4 
million for the San Marino Unified School District. Contributions are solicited 
through mailers, speeches, phone banks and events. Parents gave 58% of the 
money last year. 
</P>
<P>
 In 1991, the last time school district foundations were ranked in the state, 
the San Marino foundation raised the second-highest amount of money among 
school districts its size, according to the California Consortium of Education 
Foundations. 
</P>
<P>
 The foundation was originally formed in 1979 to provide for special programs 
and facilities. But now that state cutbacks have reduced the district's 
operating budget, the foundation will provide $500,000 for day-to-day 
operations this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
