<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN PLEADS NOT GUILTY TO MOLESTATION; COURTS: PAUL LYNN LOE WAS ARRESTED AFTER 
PHOTOGRAPHS OF A 4-YEAR-OLD GIRL BEING ABUSED WERE FOUND IN A TRASH DUMPSTER. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Rowland Heights construction worker pleaded not guilty Tuesday to charges 
that he molested a 4-year-old girl and photographed the acts. 
</P>
<P>
 Paul Lynn Loe, 46, was arraigned in Citrus Municipal Court on 10 felony counts 
of child molestation and five felony counts of possession of child pornography, 
Deputy Dist. Atty. Christine Weiss said. 
</P>
<P>
 Loe was arrested Friday by Whittier police after photographs of the girl being 
molested were found in a trash dumpster behind a Whittier motel. He is being 
held at Walnut Jail in lieu of $750,000 bail pending a Jan. 13 preliminary 
hearing. If convicted on all counts, he could face up to 29 years in prison. 
</P>
<P>
 Loe was arrested Dec. 20 on suspicion of molesting the same girl and charged 
with one count of performing a lewd act upon a minor. But he was released Dec. 
28 because detectives could not find the photographs of the molestation the 
girl had mentioned. 
</P>
<P>
 Loe's second arrest came after Jack Gray, a Whittier resident who was foraging 
through the dumpster looking for cigarette coupons, came across photographs 
that showed a girl being molested, a bedroom and the hand of a man wearing a 
ring that resembled a ring Loe wears, said Whittier police Detective Tom 
Lamping. 
</P>
<P>
 Police did not immediately realize these could be the missing photographs and 
released a photo of the child's head and shoulders to local television stations 
in hopes of identifying her. 
</P>
<P>
 Calls flooded the police station, three of which identified the girl in the 
photos as the same 4-year-old allegedly molested by Loe. He was arrested again 
Dec. 31 and made admissions about the molestation to a sheriff's deputy the 
following day, Lamping said. 
</P>
<P>
 Loe's attorney, David R. Maldonado, indicated his client was remorseful but 
said he could not comment on the alleged confession. He said Loe may enter a 
plea bargain before his Jan. 13 hearing. 
</P>
<P>
 Loe and his girlfriend shared a Rowland Heights apartment unit on Greenport 
Avenue for about six months with the 4-year-old and her mother, but were not 
related to the girl, Weiss said. Loe baby-sat the girl about once a week in 
November and December. 
</P>
<P>
 Weiss said the child's mother contacted authorities after her daughter told 
her about certain activities with Loe. Weiss said the 4-year-old told her there 
were photos taken during the molestation but the girl had no idea what Loe had 
done with them. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was just a godsend when these photos turned up," Weiss said. "It 
completely corroborates the victim's testimony." 
</P>
<P>
 Weiss alleges that Loe threw the photos away in the dumpster shortly after he 
was released after his first arrest. Loe's girlfriend told authorities the two 
were at the Whittier motel the week after Loe's first arrest and Loe left her 
alone for a few minutes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
