<HEADLINE>
<P>
INSIDE LINE: OC HIGH / STUDENT NEWS AND VIEWS; NEW DIGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 When Aliso Niguel High School in Aliso Viejo opened last fall, some students 
opted to leave Capistrano Valley High School for the new state-of-the-art (but 
still unfinished) facility. 
</P>
<P>
 So how are those students faring? It's a mixed bag, according to an article in 
the CVHS Times, the student newspaper at Capistrano Valley High. 
</P>
<P>
 "I don't like it. Nothing's ready. There is nowhere to sit at lunch and no 
cafeteria. I wish I never came here," one teen said. 
</P>
<P>
 "I like it because it seems like everyone knows everyone," said another. 
</P>
<P>
 "The facilities are nice but not completely ready. It's like Bill Clinton. All 
they do is promise and they don't perform," complained another. 
</P>
</TEXT>
