TV RATINGS; SUNDAY NIGHT LINEUP HELPS CBS WIN THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LEE MARGULIES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 CBS bounced back into the No. 1 spot in the prime-time ratings last week, the 
A.C. Nielsen Co. reported Wednesday, thanks to the network's usual strong 
Sunday night lineup. "60 Minutes" was the second highest-rated show of the 
week, "Murder, She Wrote" was fourth and sandwiched between them was CBS' 
Sunday movie, "Jane's House," starring Anne Archer and James Woods. 
</P>
<P>
 NBC finished second for the week, fueled by the Orange Bowl on Saturday and 
the debut of its action series "Viper" on Sunday.The Orange Bowl, featuring the 
nail-biting showdown between Florida State and Nebraska, was seen in about 16.8 
million households, while ABC's simultaneous coverage of the Sugar Bowl--in 
which Florida rolled over West Virginia--drew only about 4.9 million. 
</P>
<P>
 Despite finishing third for the week, ABC had five of the Top 10 programs, 
including No. 1 "Home Improvement," and it remains a close second behind CBS in 
the season-to-date standings. Southland Ratings 
