<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHAPMAN WOMEN STOP LONG SKID 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Chapman women's basketball team ended a six-game losing streak by beating 
Occidental, 93-90, in overtime Wednesday at Rush Gymnasium in Eagle Rock. 
</P>
<P>
 The Panthers (3-8) trailed by five at the half but rallied to take the lead by 
as many as seven points in the second half.Occidental used a full-court press 
to send the game into overtime. Desirie Rippy made a steal and scored with two 
seconds to left to tie it, 86-86. 
</P>
<P>
 In overtime, Chapman's Deborah Nilsen made two free throws with about 15 
seconds remaining to give the Panthers a three-point lead. Occidental could 
only manage a two-point shot attempt. 
</P>
<P>
 Melody Earle, a junior guard from Estancia High School, led Chapman with 28 
points. She made nine of 19 shots from the field and all 10 of her free throws. 
</P>
<P>
 The Panthers were 23 of 25 from the free-throw line. Occidental made only 22 
of 37. 
</P>
<P>
 Chapman's Heidi Sorour, a junior guard from Saddleback College and Loara High 
School, added 20 points. Shawna Parkinson, a freshman forward from Reedly in 
Northern California, added 12 points, nine rebounds and two blocked shots. 
</P>
