<P>
 Six candidates have picked up nomination forms for the April 12 City Council 
elections, in which three seats on the five-member panel will be contested. 
</P>
<P>
 The potential candidates have until Jan. 14 to obtain 20 signatures of 
registered voters to qualify for the election, according to San Fernando 
Assistant City Clerk Wilma Miller. 
</P>
