<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL NOTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 UC Irvine basketball players Zuri Williams and Todd Whitehead, suspended for 
the last two games because of shoplifting charges, were reinstated Wednesday, 
the school announced. 
</P>
<P>
 Williams, a junior and the starting point guard, and Whitehead, a sophomore 
guard, were suspended by Anteater Coach Rod Baker following petty theft 
citations they received Dec. 13 at South Coast Plaza. 
</P>
<P>
 Both players are eligible for Saturday night's game against Cal State 
Northridge at UCI. They sat out the Anteaters' victories over Iowa and Cal 
State Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Paul Allen has resigned as Santiago High football coach to be an assistant 
coach at Chaffey College. Allen, the Cavalier coach for four seasons, compiled 
a 9-31 record. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 San Clemente's Brian Wise and Pat Caldwell are among the entrants in the Morey 
world bodyboarding championships, which begin Saturday at Banzai Pipeline on 
Oahu's North Shore. 
</P>
<P>
 Also competing will be eight-time world champion Mike Stewart, a part-time 
Huntington Beach resident, Matt Allen of Newport Beach, Jay Reale of San 
Clemente, Tim Ross of Cypress and Jeremy Olsen of Laguna Hills. 
</P>
