<HEADLINE>
<P>
THREE AREA FOOTBALL PLAYERS NAMED TO ALL-SOUTHERN SECTION TEAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROB FERNAS, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three South Bay players -- Peninsula High offensive lineman John Welbourn, 
Mira Costa defensive lineman Phil Fonua and Hawthorne defensive back Omarr 
Morgan -- have been selected to the elite All-Southern Section football team. 
</P>
<P>
 The 25-player team, chosen by members of the media, represents the best talent 
in the section's 11 divisions. 
</P>
<P>
 Others named to the squad included record-setting quarterback Keith Smith of 
Division III champion Newbury Park, highly regarded tight end Tony Gonzalez of 
Division II runner-up Huntington Beach and quarterback Glenn Thompkins of 
Division I champion Eisenhower, winner of The Times' Glenn Davis award as the 
top player in Southern California. 
</P>
<P>
 Welbourn and Morgan were winners of The Times' South Bay lineman and back of 
the year awards. Welbourn, a 6-foot-6, 275-pound senior, was a two-way lineman 
whose blocking helped Peninsula rush for more than 300 yards a game. Morgan 
excelled at free safety for Division III runner-up Hawthorne, finishing with 
150 tackles and seven interceptions. The senior also scored 15 touchdowns as a 
running back, receiver and return specialist. 
</P>
<P>
 Fonua, a 6-2, 265-pound junior, helped Mira Costa win its first Southern 
Section football title with his play at nose tackle and fullback. He led the 
Mustangs with 18 sacks and 19 touchdowns and was named Division VII co-player 
of the year after dominating opponents in the playoffs. Fonua shared the award 
with Montclair Prep running back Wilbert Smith. 
</P>
<P>
 Fonua was one of four Mira Costa players chosen to the Division VII team. The 
others were senior offensive lineman Tate McCallister, senior defensive lineman 
Miguel Prieto and junior defensive back Dino Rossi. Redondo senior running back 
Bob Cracknell, the South Bay's leading rusher with 1,709 yards, also was 
selected. 
</P>
<P>
 Hawthorne and Peninsula, which finished 1-2 in the Bay League, each placed 
four players on the Division III team. Hawthorne was represented by Morgan, 
junior defensive back Kelvin Hunter, senior offensive lineman David Camacho and 
senior defensive lineman Daniel Dorsey. Tailback James Durroh, a repeat 
selection, joined Peninsula teammates Welbourn, senior tight end-kicker Keith 
Harter and senior linebacker Tony Persichina on the team. 
</P>
<P>
 Leuzinger was represented on the Division III squad by junior linebacker Aaron 
Williams. 
</P>
<P>
 Smith, whose 98-yard, fourth-quarter touchdown run was the highlight of 
Newbury Park's 22-14 victory over Hawthorne in the championship game, was named 
Division III player of the year. 
</P>
<P>
 Five South Bay players were selected to the Division IX team. Pioneer League 
co-champion West Torrance was represented by senior offensive lineman Ryan 
Winkler and junior free safety Jim Yates, North Torrance placed senior 
quarterback Rocky Jackson and senior running back-defensive back Lacy Watkins 
on the team, and junior defensive lineman Matt Jasik of El Segundo was also 
chosen. 
</P>
<P>
 Senior running back Jasch Janowicz of division champion Atascadero was named 
Division IX player of the year. 
</P>
<P>
 Serra senior linebacker Milford Kinnard was selected to the Division VIII team 
and two-way lineman Bryan Luxembourger of division runner-up Costa Mesa was 
named player of the year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
