<P>
PRO FOOTBALL DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE NFL; REDSKINS CAN'T TALK TO TURNER YET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Washington Redskins are interested in Dallas offensive coordinator Norv 
Turner as their new coach, but NFL rules prohibit them from talking to Turner 
until the Cowboys have been eliminated from the playoffs. . . . Houston 
defensive coordinator Buddy Ryan said he is interested in either of the 
coaching vacancies at Washington or Atlanta. . . . Detroit running back Barry 
Sanders, who sprained his left knee in a Thanksgiving Day loss to the Chicago 
Bears, practiced for the first time Wednesday and might start Saturday when the 
Lions play host to Green Bay in a first-round NFC playoff game. 
</P>
