COMMUNITY DIGEST: THE REGION; HOMEOWNERS WARNED OF FAKE PLUMBING INSPECTORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Reports of people posing as water company workers have prompted the San 
Gabriel Valley Water Co. to alert its 45,000 customers in Whittier, Montebello, 
Hacienda Heights and the San Gabriel Valley to beware of anyone asking to enter 
a home to inspect the plumbing. 
</P>
<P>
 The alert followed complaints last year about thefts by people who represented 
themselves as water company employees to enter houses. 
</P>
<P>
 The El Monte-based utility is notifying its customers that normally a water 
company employee would not ask to enter a house. This would happen only if a 
customer had previously contacted the company. Company officials also said any 
questions about whether someone is an employee can be directed to the customer 
service office at (818) 448-6183. 
</P>
